<TITLE> EC starts checking voter lists </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Moinul Hoque Chowdhury bdnews24.com correspondent Dhaka, Sept 2 (bdnews24.com) - The Election Commission has begun the process of correcting any flaws in voter lists across the country. The work will continue throughout the month according to the EC's timeline, for publishing the final voter list in October, an election official said. District election officers, upazila and thana election officers and assistant registration officers have been given guidelines to scrutinise seven components of each entry on the voter listsincluding voter name, gender, number, area code and photographto detect any flaws. They have been asked to send weekly reports on their progress to the commission, EC secretariat deputy secretary Mihir Sarwar Murshed told bdnews24.com on Tuesday. Several district election officers told bdnews24.com they have already started the work of correcting mistakes. The Election Commission formally completed voter registration throughout the country in July. About eight crore voters were registered. Meanwhile, a total of 44 political parties have collected application forms for registering with the Election Commission up to Tuesday, EC sources said. The distribution and submission of registration forms that began on Aug 27 will continue till Oct 15. bdnews
